{"questionId":"33022682","questionHtml":"<p>Show that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi></math> is a palindromic polynomial.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mi>n</mi></msup><mi>p</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>x</mi></mfrac></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>q</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mi>m</mi></msup><mi>q</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>x</mi></mfrac></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempts to substitute for&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></math>&nbsp; and&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>q</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></math>&nbsp; into&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>p</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mi>q</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong><em>(M1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mi>n</mi></msup><mi>p</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>x</mi></mfrac></mfenced><msup><mi>x</mi><mi>m</mi></msup><mi>q</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>x</mi></mfrac></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>m</mi></mrow></msup><mi>p</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>x</mi></mfrac></mfenced><mi>q</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>x</mi></mfrac></mfenced></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>m</mi></mrow></msup><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>x</mi></mfrac></mfenced></math> &nbsp; (and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>m</mi></math> is the degree of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi></math>)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>hence <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi></math> is a palindromic polynomial.&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>x</mi></mfrac></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>p</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mi>n</mi></msup></mfrac></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>q</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>x</mi></mfrac></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>q</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mi>m</mi></msup></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong> (A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempts to substitute for&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>x</mi></mfrac></mfenced></math>&nbsp; and&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>q</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>x</mi></mfrac></mfenced></math>&nbsp; into&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>x</mi></mfrac></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>p</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>x</mi></mfrac></mfenced><mi>q</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>x</mi></mfrac></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong><em>(M1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>x</mi></mfrac></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>p</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mi>n</mi></msup></mfrac><mfrac><mrow><mi>q</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mi>m</mi></msup></mfrac><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>p</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mi>q</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>m</mi></mrow></msup></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>m</mi></mrow></msup><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>x</mi></mfrac></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>p</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mi>q</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></math> &nbsp; and &nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>p</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mi>q</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></math> &nbsp; (and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>m</mi></math> is the degree of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi></math>)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong><em>A1</em></strong></p>\n<p>hence <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi></math> is a palindromic polynomial.&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 3</strong></p>\n<p>for example,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>a</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><msup><mi>x</mi><mi>n</mi></msup><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>a</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>+</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>a</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>a</mi><mi>n</mi></msub></math> &nbsp; AND</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>q</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>b</mi><mi>m</mi></msub><msup><mi>x</mi><mi>m</mi></msup><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>b</mi><mrow><mi>m</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mi>m</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>+</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>b</mi><mrow><mi>m</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>b</mi><mi>m</mi></msub></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong><em>A1</em></strong></p>\n<p>attempts to multiple out their&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mi>q</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong>(M1)</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Only award <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em> for polynomials of degree <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>m</mi></math> respectively with different corresponding coefficients.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mi>q</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>a</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><msub><mi>b</mi><mi>m</mi></msub><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mi>m</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>n</mi></mrow></msup><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mrow><msub><mi>a</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><msub><mi>b</mi><mi>m</mi></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>a</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><msub><mi>b</mi><mrow><mi>m</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mfenced><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mi>m</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>+</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mrow><msub><mi>a</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><msub><mi>b</mi><mi>m</mi></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>a</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><msub><mi>b</mi><mrow><mi>m</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mfenced><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>a</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><msub><mi>b</mi><mi>m</mi></msub></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong><em>A1A1</em></strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <strong><em>A1</em></strong> for the first and second terms and <strong><em>A1</em></strong> for the penultimate and last terms.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>hence <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi></math> is a palindromic polynomial&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[4 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"33022682","referenceCode":"24N.3.AHL.TZ0.2e","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Show that f is a palindromic polynomial.","paper":"3","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"e","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.6—Simple proof"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}